id: pm-todos-auvq
title: Add native todo-state import/export support
description: "Make pm-todos import/export pm items to the pi coding-agent todo extension state format, keep markdown/todo.txt behavior working, verify against pm CLI 2026.6.9, and avoid duplicate pm items."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[2]: pm-todos,todo-import-export
created_at: "2026-06-09T18:53:22.670Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-09T19:03:43.055Z"
author: codex
resolution: "Added todojson import/export support for pi coding-agent TodoDetails, defaulted todojson imports to idempotent upsert matching, removed redundant import/export command registrations, and aligned package metadata with pm CLI/SDK 2026.6.9."
expected_result: pm-todos can import/export pm items to the upstream todo tool state format and repeated todojson imports do not create duplicate pm items.
actual_result: "Temp pm workspace with local package install: first todojson import created 2 items, second import updated 2 and created 0, list-all stayed at 2 items, export returned valid TodoDetails JSON, and package doctor reported no warnings."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-09T19:00:51.740Z",codex,"Implemented pi coding-agent todo state import/export as --format todojson. The format accepts upstream TodoDetails { action, todos, nextId } or a raw Todo[] array, maps text/done to pm title/status, defaults todojson import to upsert so repeated imports do not duplicate pm items, and exports TodoDetails JSON with sequential ids. Removed redundant explicit todos import/export command registrations so native importer/exporter routes no longer self-collide in pm package doctor. Verified no credential-shaped secrets in package-owned source/history; npm pack allowlist contains only dist/docs/manifest/package metadata."
files[4]{path,scope,note}:
  index.ts,project,todojson import/export implementation
  package.json,project,pm CLI SDK 2026.6.9 metadata
  README.md,project,todojson user docs
  test/formats.test.ts,project,todojson parser serializer validation tests
tests[2]{command,path,scope,timeout_seconds,pm_context_mode,env_set,env_clear,shared_host_safe,assert_stdout_contains,assert_stdout_regex,assert_stderr_contains,assert_stderr_regex,assert_stdout_min_lines,assert_json_field_equals,assert_json_field_gte,note}:
